    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-05-26T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-05-26T17:00:00-05:00" n="598"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d598">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">821.6363/398: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Piles</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-05-26T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 26, 1928—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>36. Department’s telegram No. 24, May 25, 1 p.m. Today I returned the memorandum
                    in person to the President. He stated that the Ministry of Industry contends
                    that the decree should not be suspended as a whole and wishes time to present a
                    report, [omission?] declaring the President now has and will consider carefully
                    on Monday and hopes to issue an order next Tuesday which will embody his
                    personal views.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Piles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
